## Current story

**ID:** STORY-016
**Title:** Menu bar live Pomodoro countdown
**Description:** Add an NSStatusItem in the macOS menu bar that shows the active Pomodoro countdown (e.g. '🍅 18:42') in real time. Clicking it shows a mini popover with pause/stop controls and the current task title. When no timer is running, show the hourglass icon only.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- NSStatusItem appears in menu bar whenever Timed is running
- While timer is active, title updates every second showing MM:SS remaining
- Clicking the status item opens a compact popover: task title, time remaining, pause/resume button, stop button
- When timer is not running, status item shows '⏳' with no countdown
- On break, shows '☕ 04:30' style label
- swift build passes

**Implementation notes:**
Create MenuBarController.swift. Use NSStatusBar.system.statusItem(withLength: NSStatusItem.variableLength). Observe FocusTimerModel via @MainActor. Use a Timer.scheduledTimer on main runloop to update the button title every second. Popover: NSPopover containing a small SwiftUI view wrapping FocusTimerWidget. Instantiate MenuBarController in TimeManagerDesktopApp and keep a strong reference.

